<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="364" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,764,1980]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,764,791]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Male imago: 1) general coloration: thorax brown and abdomen yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1278,765,791]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1996]" captionTargetBox="[194,1400,179,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1406,166,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov., male imago: A) body (lateral view); B) body (dorsal view); C) forewing; D) hind wing (enlarged); E) hind wing; F) genitalia (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3460208/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
A–B); 2) hind wing with costal projection almost forming right angle, located approximately half distance from base to apex of wing (
<figureCitation box="[224,302,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1996]" captionTargetBox="[194,1400,179,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1406,166,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov., male imago: A) body (lateral view); B) body (dorsal view); C) forewing; D) hind wing (enlarged); E) hind wing; F) genitalia (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3460208/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
D–E); 3) abdominal terga yellowish brown, VIII and X washed brown, IX washed with dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[159,238,873,899]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1996]" captionTargetBox="[194,1400,179,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1406,166,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov., male imago: A) body (lateral view); B) body (dorsal view); C) forewing; D) hind wing (enlarged); E) hind wing; F) genitalia (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3460208/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
A–B); 4) penis projection lanceolate, straight, and of short size (less than half of the total length of penis lobes), anteriorly directed (
<figureCitation box="[454,539,909,935]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1996]" captionTargetBox="[194,1400,179,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1406,166,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov., male imago: A) body (lateral view); B) body (dorsal view); C) forewing; D) hind wing (enlarged); E) hind wing; F) genitalia (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3460208/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
); 5) penis lobes fused on basal half, separated by a distance approximately twice the width of one penis lobe, with a shallow concavity in the junction of the lobes (
<figureCitation box="[1070,1156,945,971]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1996]" captionTargetBox="[194,1400,179,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1406,166,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov., male imago: A) body (lateral view); B) body (dorsal view); C) forewing; D) hind wing (enlarged); E) hind wing; F) genitalia (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3460208/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="364" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,764,1980]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,980,1007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Description</emphasis>
. Male imago (n=6): Length of body: 5.0– 
<quantity box="[822,913,980,1007]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" unit="mm" value="5.4">5.4 mm</quantity>
; forewings: 
<quantity box="[1056,1196,980,1007]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="6.2" metricValueMin="5.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="6.2" valueMin="5.8">5.8–6.2 mm</quantity>
; hind wings: 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" unit="mm" value="0.75" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.7">0.7–0.8 mm</quantity>
. General color brown with yellowish brown areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,764,1980]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[278,359,1053,1079]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1996]" captionTargetBox="[194,1400,179,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1406,166,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov., male imago: A) body (lateral view); B) body (dorsal view); C) forewing; D) hind wing (enlarged); E) hind wing; F) genitalia (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3460208/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
A–B). General coloration orangish brown. Scape and pedicel light brown. Ocelli white, surrounded by dark brown ring at base. Eyes black, turbinate portion orangish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,764,1980]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[297,376,1125,1151]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1996]" captionTargetBox="[194,1400,179,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1406,166,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov., male imago: A) body (lateral view); B) body (dorsal view); C) forewing; D) hind wing (enlarged); E) hind wing; F) genitalia (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3460208/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
A–B). General coloration yellowish brown. Pro- and mesonota dark brown. Mesonotum with longitudinal medial, medioparapsidal suture light brown, scutellum darker. Metanotum light brown (
<figureCitation box="[1274,1362,1161,1187]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1996]" captionTargetBox="[194,1400,179,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1406,166,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov., male imago: A) body (lateral view); B) body (dorsal view); C) forewing; D) hind wing (enlarged); E) hind wing; F) genitalia (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3460208/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Sterna light brown. Wing membranes hyaline. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[750,836,1197,1223]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1996]" captionTargetBox="[194,1400,179,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1406,166,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov., male imago: A) body (lateral view); B) body (dorsal view); C) forewing; D) hind wing (enlarged); E) hind wing; F) genitalia (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3460208/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
) with yellowish brown veins and cross veins hyaline; basal third of costal vein brown; fork of vein MP slightly asymmetric. Hind wing with costal projection well-developed, almost forming right angle, located approximately half distance from base to apex of wing (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1368,1269,1295]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1996]" captionTargetBox="[194,1400,179,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1406,166,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov., male imago: A) body (lateral view); B) body (dorsal view); C) forewing; D) hind wing (enlarged); E) hind wing; F) genitalia (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3460208/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
D–E); veins yellowish brown, except base of vein C to costal projection brown; apical lower portion of hind wing tinged with brown (
<figureCitation box="[300,379,1341,1367]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1996]" captionTargetBox="[194,1400,179,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1406,166,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov., male imago: A) body (lateral view); B) body (dorsal view); C) forewing; D) hind wing (enlarged); E) hind wing; F) genitalia (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3460208/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
D–E). Coxae brown and trochanters yellowish brown. Foreleg: femur yellowish brown with apical region brown; tibia yellowish brown, basal region brown; tarsi yellowish brown. Mid- and hindlegs similar to forelegs, except for usual differences.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,764,1980]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[325,391,1449,1475]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[232,1359,184,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[217,1370,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1A–C. Distribution and sampled sites of Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov: A) Map of South America, highlighting the collection sites of Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov. in Tocantins state; B) Cavalo Queimado waterfall, rio da Conceição, Tocantins state; C) Sono river, Pedro afonso, Tocantins state." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3460206/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
): Terga yellowish brown, VIII and X washed brown; IX washed with dark brown. Sterna yellowish brown. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[441,530,1485,1511]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1996]" captionTargetBox="[194,1400,179,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1406,166,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Simothraulopsis primus sp. nov., male imago: A) body (lateral view); B) body (dorsal view); C) forewing; D) hind wing (enlarged); E) hind wing; F) genitalia (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3460208/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
): Styliger plate yellowish brown. Forceps segment I, II and III brown. Segment II 0.11 length of segment I, 1.05 length of segment III. Penis lobes yellowish brown, fused on basal half, inner margins divergent; each lobe rounded apically, but appearing almost pointed, separated by distance approximately twice width of one penis lobe, with straight lanceolate portion having short size (less than half of total length of penis lobes) projection, anteriorly directed and narrowing towards apex; inner margins of lobes divergent. Caudal filaments unknown (broken and lost).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="364" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,764,1980]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1701,1727]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Etymology.</emphasis>
